gomodel:SYNGO_1085  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Pre-embedding immuno-peroxidase labelling for electron microscopy indicates the presence of Alpha2C Adrenergic receptor (Alpha2C-AR) immunoreactivity in dendrites in the nucleus locus coeruleus. Alpha2C-AR immunoreactivity was often associated with plasma membrane regions apposed to astrocytes or presynaptic terminals, and frequently adjacent to postsynaptic densities (Fig. 2B, 3B). However, immunoreactivity was also found at a distance from the PSD at the membrane as well as in the cytoplasm of dendrites and endomembranes.\n\nPreabsorption of the antibody with the peptide completely abolishes immunostaining (Fig. 1B).. Experimental description: Four adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (200-250 g; Hill-top Labs, Scottdale, PA) were used in this study." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1085" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

